<!-- MainCellStart --><TD VALIGN='TOP'><CENTER><table border=0 cellpadding=5 bgcolor=#DDDDDD width=50% background='/images/table-head-bg.jpg'><tr><td background=''><table border=0 cellpadding=5 bgcolor=#BB0000 width=100%><tr><td width=50% background='/images/table-bg.jpg'><b><font size=+3 color=#FFF000><center>EverMon News<center></font></b></td></tr></table></td></tr></table></center><HR SIZE=1 WIDTH=80%></CENTER><BR><TABLE BORDER=0 CELLSPACING=0 CELLPADDING=5 COLS=1 WIDTH='80%' BACKGROUND='barback.jpg'><TR><TD><B><FONT COLOR='#FFFFCC' SIZE=+2>Friday, December 31st, 1999</FONT></B></TD></TR></TABLE><BR><B><FONT SIZE=+1>09:50 - EverLore to sponsor EverNews</FONT></B><BLOCKQUOTE>
The EverLore team (<A href='http://www.everlore.com'>http://www.everlore.com</a>) has agreed to help sponsor the
upcoming EverNews utility (which is part of EverTools) by providing EQ News
information.  EverLore will also be hosting historical player load information
for EQ game servers, which will be used by the new EverMon 3.0 software. We
are ver excited about this new partnership between the two teams, and the
new services both teams will be able to provide.<BR><BR>

EverNews is one of several small EverQuest utilities that will appear as part
of the upcoming EverTools project. Watch for more information on this, and
other EverTool utilities over the coming weeks on this website, and our
EverTools development and support e-mail list<BR><BR>
<B>- <A HREF='mailto:bryonq@hydracomp.com'>Zackron</A></B></BLOCKQUOTE><TABLE BORDER=0 CELLSPACING=0 CELLPADDING=5 COLS=1 WIDTH='80%' BACKGROUND='barback.jpg'><TR><TD><B><FONT COLOR='#FFFFCC' SIZE=+2>Tuesday, December 7th, 1999</FONT></B></TD></TR></TABLE><BR><B><FONT SIZE=+1>16:55 - EverTools Development Team</FONT></B><BLOCKQUOTE>
EverMon is growing into EverTools.  As such, I am currently looking for some additional members for the EverTools development team.<BR><BR>

Job Requirments :<BR>
    * Strong working knowledge of Microsoft Visual Basic 6.0<BR>
    * Familiarity with using low level windows API<BR>
    * Works well in a team environment<BR>
    * Not looking for much pay (o.k. any pay *smile*)<BR><BR>

If you feel you would like to help out with the development of EverTools, please send me an e-mail to bryonq@hydracomp.com, include in it why you would like to be part of the development team, and to what end you feel you can contribute to it.  Thanks!<BR><BR>
With Special thanks to both the Stratics Network (<a href="www.stratics.com">www.stratics.com</a>)
<B>- <A HREF='mailto:bryonq@hydracomp.com'>Zackron</A></B></BLOCKQUOTE><TABLE BORDER=0 CELLSPACING=0 CELLPADDING=5 COLS=1 WIDTH='80%' BACKGROUND='barback.jpg'><TR><TD><B><FONT COLOR='#FFFFCC' SIZE=+2>Friday, December 3rd, 1999</FONT></B></TD></TR></TABLE><BR><B><FONT SIZE=+1>16:52 - Chat Servers Back!</FONT></B><BLOCKQUOTE>
With Special thanks to both the Stratics Network (<a href="www.stratics.com">www.stratics.com</a>)
and the DreamMyst Network (<a href="www.dreammyst.net">www.dreammyst.net</a>), EverMon Clients
now have a new set of IRC servers to call home! As such, everyone should see
the Interactive Menu become avalible again from within EverMon.<BR><BR>

For now, EverMon will only be using one of the networks, however, EverMon 3.0
will be set up to use multiple networks, which will allow for load sharing
between them.  This way during patch days, the IRC servers should not get
over-crowded.<BR><BR>

<B>- <A HREF='mailto:bryonq@hydracomp.com'>Zackron</A></B></BLOCKQUOTE><TABLE BORDER=0 CELLSPACING=0 CELLPADDING=5 COLS=1 WIDTH='80%' BACKGROUND='barback.jpg'><TR><TD><B><FONT COLOR='#FFFFCC' SIZE=+2>Thursday, December 2nd, 1999</FONT></B></TD></TR></TABLE><BR><B><FONT SIZE=+1>16:52 - Chat Network Gone?</FONT></B><BLOCKQUOTE>
The IRC chat network (irc.gamenode.net) that EverMon uses to allow people to
chat with each other seems to have disappeared.  This is why the Interactive
menu no longer appears in EverMon.  As such, I am in the process of trying
to find a new IRC chat network backbone for EverMon to use.  If you are the
administrator of an IRC chat network that you would like to allow EverMon
to use, Or if you have a dedicated NT-Based server that I could run a
custom EverMon chat server on, please let me know... Thanks!<BR><BR>
<B>- <A HREF='mailto:bryonq@hydracomp.com'>Zackron</A></B></BLOCKQUOTE><TABLE BORDER=0 CELLSPACING=0 CELLPADDING=5 COLS=1 WIDTH='80%' BACKGROUND='barback.jpg'><TR><TD><B><FONT COLOR='#FFFFCC' SIZE=+2>Thursday, December 2nd, 1999</FONT></B></TD></TR></TABLE><BR><B><FONT SIZE=+1>15:41 - Take the EverMon User Survey</FONT></B><BLOCKQUOTE>
With all the great feedback I recieved, I took the time to create a user
survey to allow me to get a better idea of what EverMon users would like
to see in EverMon 3.0.  Please take a few moments, and fill out the
server here : <a href=em_survey.asp>EverMon User Survey</a><BR><BR>

<B>- <A HREF='mailto:bryonq@hydracomp.com'>Zackron</A></B></BLOCKQUOTE><TABLE BORDER=0 CELLSPACING=0 CELLPADDING=5 COLS=1 WIDTH='80%' BACKGROUND='barback.jpg'><TR><TD><B><FONT COLOR='#FFFFCC' SIZE=+2>Monday, November 22nd, 1999</FONT></B></TD></TR></TABLE><BR><B><FONT SIZE=+1>13:30 - EverMon 3.0 in development - feature request</FONT></B><BLOCKQUOTE>
I'm currently in the process of re-writting all of my low level libraries.
As a result, EverMon is going to need to be re-written as well.  Since it
needs to be re-written, I figured this would be an excellent time to release
EverMon 3.0.  If you have any feature suggestions that you would like to
see included in the new 3.0 version, please send them to me via e-mail to
<a href='mailto:bryonq@hydracomp.com'>bryonq@hydracomp.com</a>.  Thanks!<BR><BR>
<B>- <A HREF='mailto:bryonq@hydracomp.com'>Zackron</A></B></BLOCKQUOTE><TABLE BORDER=0 CELLSPACING=0 CELLPADDING=5 COLS=1 WIDTH='80%' BACKGROUND='barback.jpg'><TR><TD><B><FONT COLOR='#FFFFCC' SIZE=+2>Friday, July 2nd, 1999</FONT></B></TD></TR></TABLE><BR><B><FONT SIZE=+1>15:21 - EverMon/EverMonBeta 2.1 Build 44 Released</FONT></B><BLOCKQUOTE>
A small patch as been released for EverMon and EverMonBeta.  This should fix
a crashing problem that resulted after the last server was added to EverMon
from the EverQuest Stat Server.  This should also allow the correct servers
to be monitored when selected from the Monitor and Events Option menu within
EverMon<br><br>

Remember, you will always get the latest version of EverMon while using the
Launcher to start EverMon.  If you need to download the Launcher, select
the 'Download' link to the left of this page, for download and installation
instructions.<br><br>
<B>- <A HREF='mailto:bryonq@hydracomp.com'>Zackron</A></B></BLOCKQUOTE><br><hr width=80% size=1><br><center><a href='/default.asp'><img src='/images/logoblack.jpg' border=0 alt='Home' width=50 height=38></a></center></table></table></center></BODY></HTML>
